review_blob: ARCHIVE: On tap at the brewery. Clear, light orange in color. Smells sweet and boozy. Very creamy. You can clearly taste the birch. Also very clear is the 10.2% ABV. Nice beer.
12 oz can into glass. Hazy copper color, thin off-white head. Nice hop aroma. A bit biscuit like on the end. Finishes quite clean. Another hit from SKA.

12 oz can into glass. Lots of roasted malt in aroma and flavor. Very thin mouthfeel. Almost no head. I wish these guys could make some bigger stuff. This would translate well with a higher ABV, but at 4% it doesnt do it for me.
I love this beer. Fruity and dry. Perfect porch pounder on a hot, dry Colorado summer day. Goes down very fast.
